data.title: Good Coffee... That's it!
data.text: I visited this place a couple months ago, the service was average. We asked for three empanadas and three coffees. The empanadas were burnt, really hard to bite but the coffees were AWESOME! If I visit this place once again it'll just be for the coffee, nothing more.

data.title: Cant say that it was all I thought they would be!
data.text: I agree with the previous comment of the customer service, they have absolutely none, they are not rude they just don't treat you like the person that is keeping your business alive. They take forever to bring the food over to the table, I was not happy with this kind of service, I thought it was a little to long to wait for service, when there was only another couple there, I cannot imagine what it will be like if the place had more people there!

data.title: The most terrible experience of my life
data.text: Firts time here, because I have a friend that she recomend me this place, the costumer service was REALLY BAD, when they take the order, they take aproximatelly like 40 minutes to bring the food and i think that maybe more than 40 minutes, the food that i ordered was a mixed barbecue, the meat was burned, I tell to the waiter that the meat was burned, He said "that he was not the chef", I think that not was the form to answer me, I felt that the two persons that give me the services they don't pay attention to us, I don't recomend this place, I never will go again 0% of 100%.

data.title: La mejor comida venezolana en Kisimmee y Orlando
data.text: He tenido la oportunidad de probar diferentes platos, las arepas de carne asada son excelentes, al igual que los patacones, a mi esposa le encantan las arepas de pollo y la sopas que varian dia a dia, mis hijos estan encantados con las empanadas de pollo y los tequeños, un lugar para degustar los sabores de venezuela con buen precio
